  "text": "There was a negative association between proximity to ethnic markets and supermarkets from home address and BMI only for women and, on the other hand, a positive association between neighbourhood density of grocery stores and BMI also only for women [CITATION_1] . A further study detected a significant positive association between number of specialty stores and overweight or obesity only for women, too. The same study found an inverse association between green space and overweight or obesity for women and a positive association for men, however. Moreover, a significant positive association between summer outdoor facilities and the two outcomes of overweight and obesity was also only detected for women [CITATION_2] .",
